<dl id="n05073j"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05073j">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05073j"> 73(j)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> classics / they adore Homer</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The same frame of mind finds support in the usual grammar-school admiration for the two classical languages and their literatures. People were taught to look down upon modern languages as mere dialects or <i>patois</i> and to worship Greek and Latin. <small> Otto Jespersen, <a name="OJLN" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#OJLN"><cite title="source">Language: its Nature, Development and Origin</cite></a> (Jan 1922) 321</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
